        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 3:46AM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 345 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Artas to 9 miles northeast of Java to 6
miles northeast of Lowry. Movement was east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ipswich, Eureka, Selby, Bowdle, Leola, Roscoe, Hosmer, Pembrook
Colony, Java, Deerfield Colony, Plainview Colony, Long Lake, Artas,
Lowry, Hillsview, Loyalton, Lake Hiddenwood Rec Area, Greenway,
Cravens Corner, and New Town Corner.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT for
north central South Dakota.</instruction>
